{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TrKeHd3EbQY39Vb89rSVna","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# handlers\n2\t\n3\tPurpose: HTTP CRUD handler layer for the user service — routes incoming requests to store operations and encodes JSON responses.\n4\t\n5\tTags: api, interface\n6\t\n7\t## Overview\n8\t\n9\tThe `handlers` package wires four REST endpoints (`POST /users`, `GET /users/{id}`, `PUT /users/{id}`, `DELETE /users/{id}`) onto a `*http.ServeMux`. It depends on the `Store` interface rather than the concrete store type, keeping the two packages loosely coupled and independently testable.\n10\t\n11\t## File Index\n12\t\n13\t| File | Description | Doc |\n14\t|------|-------------|-----|\n15\t| `handlers.go` | `Handler` struct, `Store` interface, route registration, and per-verb handler functions | [handlers.go.md](handlers.go.md) |\n16\t\n17\t## Constraints and Notes\n18\t\n19\t- **Interface boundary:** `Handler` accepts any `Store` implementation; the production wiring in `main.go` passes `*store.Store`, but tests may supply a lightweight stub without importing the store package.\n20\t- **Go 1.22 routing:** `RegisterRoutes` relies on method-prefixed patterns (e.g. `\"POST /users\"`) introduced in Go 1.22. The service will not compile against earlier toolchains.\n21\t- **No middleware:** Request logging, authentication, and recovery are not handled here; they must be layered at the `ServeMux` level by the caller (`main.go`).\n22\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"35257aad-63bc-4cf0-8ffd-7e53eb3322fb","uuid":"33260f2f-bd38-4cb8-8d7c-c9e2490d16e4","timestamp":"2026-04-05T22:44:27.149Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/establish-regression-recordings/sandbox/regressions/doc-user-service/output/internal/userservice/handlers/README.md","content":"# handlers\n\nPurpose: HTTP CRUD handler layer for the user service — routes incoming requests to store operations and encodes JSON responses.\n\nTags: api, interface\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `handlers` package wires four REST endpoints (`POST /users`, `GET /users/{id}`, `PUT /users/{id}`, `DELETE /users/{id}`) onto a `*http.ServeMux`. It depends on the `Store` interface rather than the concrete store type, keeping the two packages loosely coupled and independently testable.\n\n## File Index\n\n| File | Description | Doc |\n|------|-------------|-----|\n| `handlers.go` | `Handler` struct, `Store` interface, route registration, and per-verb handler functions | [handlers.go.md](handlers.go.md) |\n\n## Constraints and Notes\n\n- **Interface boundary:** `Handler` accepts any `Store` implementation; the production wiring in `main.go` passes `*store.Store`, but tests may supply a lightweight stub without importing the store package.\n- **Go 1.22 routing:** `RegisterRoutes` relies on method-prefixed patterns (e.g. `\"POST /users\"`) introduced in Go 1.22. The service will not compile against earlier toolchains.\n- **No middleware:** Request logging, authentication, and recovery are not handled here; they must be layered at the `ServeMux` level by the caller (`main.go`).\n","numLines":22,"startLine":1,"totalLines":22}}}
